<section xml:id="section-constant-factor-rule">
    <title>The Constant Factor Rule</title>

    <p>The next rule you are going to practice is the <term>constant factor rule</term> of differentiation.  This is another rule you do in your head. <men>\lzoo{x}{k\ \fe{f}{x}}=k\cdot\lzoo{x}{\fe{f}{x}}\quad\text{for }k\in\reals\text{.}</men></p>

            <p>In the following examples and problems several derivative rules are used that are shown in <xref ref="appendix-derivative-formulas"/>.  While working this lab you should refer to those rules; you may want to cover up the chain rule and implicit derivative columns this week!  You should make a goal of having all of the basic formulas memorized within a week.</p>

